{
  "answer": "**In *Diwan-E-Ghalib* (Mirza Ghalib), chapter 100 is a ghazal whose title is the matla itself: \"Kaaba mein jaa raha toh na do ta'na kya kahein\"** (transliteration).[^1]\n\nThe full **matla** (opening couplet) reads:\n\n> Kaaba mein jaa raha toh na do ta'na kya kahein  \n> Bhoola hoon haq-e-sohbat-e-ahl-e-kunisht ko[^2]\n\nIn English translation:\n\n> Don't mock my path toward the holy site, you see,  \n> The tavern's fellowship is lost to me.[^3]\n\n[^1]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 100, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/transliteration/).\n[^2]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 100, [p-eab6eb](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/transliteration/#p-eab6eb).\n[^3]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 100, [p-fa6504](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/100-kaaba-mein-jaa-raha-toh-na-do-tana-kya-kahein/translation/#p-fa6504).",
